			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Does anyone have a trivia plugin for IGN bot, or one that could be adapted for IGN bot? If not, anyone with some PHP background interested in helping me put one together?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Looking for something like ...
<br />

<br />
!start trivia 
<br />

<br />
[triviabot] Trivia has begun, please do /tell triviabot !include to participate.
<br />

<br />
[triviabot] Trivia question .....[answer a] [answer b] [answer c] [answer d]
<br />

<br />
** if noone gets the right answer ...
<br />

<br />
[triviabot] Noone answered correctly, try a new question.
<br />

<br />
** if someone gets the right answer ...
<br />

<br />
[triviabot] Congratulations! **soandso** has answered correctly.
<br />

<br />
** start a new question ....
<br />

<br />

<br />
[triviabot] Trivia question ... etc etc
<br />

<br />
** if someone picks the wrong one ...
<br />

<br />
from [triviabot] I am sorry, that is not correct. You are excluded from the remainder of the question time. (this in tells so as not to set off the other players)
<br />

<br />
Have the bot give 1 point per correct question, 0 points for a wrong answer.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Set a time of say 60 seconds per question.
<br />

<br />
Would need a few commands ...
<br />

<br />
!set trivia sponser (need 1 person in charge of the event)
<br />

<br />
!suspend xxplayer (for that annoying player that shouts out the answer in chat and ruins it for the others, this would only be valid until this session ends)
<br />

<br />
!end trivia (ends the session and allows the sponser to award points) A link to a popup should come up when !end trivia is triggered, this should display who participated and how many points each finished with.
<br />

<br />
Would be nice if this information could then be filed away as a log maybe? that could be retrieved with a "!past trivia" command.
<br />

<br />
All the values need to be reset when the next session starts.
<br />

<br />
The concept here would be that the sponser would need to have credits set aside for the awards. Say 100,000 for 1st, 50,000 for 2nd and 10,000 for 3rd. These are just idea numbers, could be any amount the sponser wishes to use. They would need to announce the prizes at the begining of the event.
<br />

<br />
!set award1 xxamount (enter amount of 1st prize)
<br />
!set award2 xxamount (enter amount of 2nd prize)
<br />
!set award3 xxamount (enter amount of 3rd prize)
<br />

<br />
** Could maybe have a window popup for the sponser with information on how to do this part when they trigger the start of event. Perhaps "start trivia" triggers this popup and "!begin trivia" actually starts the question sequence.
<br />

<br />
I am just going by credits here, but I suppose items could also be used as awards. Just enter the item name instead of xxamount.
<br />

<br />
Would also need some command to enable me to enter in new questions and answers ... each question and answers should probably have a identifier, so that the bot when selecting the next question doesn't pick the same one or one that has already been used during that session.
<br />

<br />
Hmm, strangly enough, sounds like I might be able to take a raidbot and revamp the raid features to this, might have to attempt that if no responses.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
