				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">heh well I'd be more than willing to enter the questions and answers into the database, and theres no time limit on it anyway, so can take as long as needed. 
<br />

<br />
If theres a command in the code to enter the questions and answers, it makes it even better, then can add them on the fly over time. I would like to make questions and answers based on the game iteself. I was thinking perhaps 100 questions based on Rubi-Kai only, then 100 on Notum Wars, then 100 on Shadowlands, then 100 on Alien Invasion when it comes out. Then over time add more to each section.
<br />

<br />
could maybe have an input like ...
<br />

<br />

<br />
Expansion :::  Question ::: Answer(a)**(correct answer) ::: Answer(b) ::: Answer(c) ::: Answer(d)
<br />

<br />
!addition RK, Question, answera(*), answerb, aswerc, answerd
<br />

<br />
Course, would need to have the bot throwout the 4 answers in a random sequence, if it always but them in the same sequence, it would to easy to answer it after it has been seen a couple times.
<br />

<br />
Also after some thought, this doesn't need to be a plugin for IGN, it can be a standalone code, I have all the source codes for a basicbot, helpbot, raidnet bot, IGN bot etc, so can be used in any of the formats. I also have MySQL setup as well as PHP4, so can even be done that way.
<br />

<br />
Also, it could be made in a flatfile format, like IGN is. Then all the questions and answers would have to be entered into the filelog individually.
<br />

<br />
Lot of options here really and I have many more ideas for it, but I don't have the knowledge currently to write the PHP code needed. I am learning it, but going to take awhile <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
